1
00:00:17,845 --> 00:00:19,278
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're lost in the dark.</font>

2
00:02:27,063 --> 00:02:29,227
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one else sees it.</font>

3
00:02:32,383 --> 00:02:33,899
<font color="#FFFFFF">This thing in me.</font>

4
00:02:39,818 --> 00:02:42,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">Even I didn't see it at first.</font>

5
00:02:45,425 --> 00:02:48,575
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then, one day, it was there.</font>

6
00:02:53,461 --> 00:02:55,696
<font color="#FFFFFF">A stain.</font>

7
00:03:03,147 --> 00:03:05,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the more
I thought about it...</font>

8
00:03:05,896 --> 00:03:09,855
<font color="#FFFFFF">the more I realized I couldn't
remember a time it wasn't there.</font>

9
00:03:09,923 --> 00:03:11,954
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>While we're here
toasting you and your legacy</i></font>

10
00:03:12,021 --> 00:03:13,492
<font color="#FFFFFF">- <i>of humanitarian aid...</i>
- Invisible to everyone.</font>

11
00:03:13,522 --> 00:03:14,946
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>What was it Plutarch said?</i></font>

12
00:03:15,014 --> 00:03:16,607
<font color="#FFFFFF">Except you.</font>

13
00:03:17,318 --> 00:03:19,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">You saw right through it,
didn't you?</font>

14
00:03:19,278 --> 00:03:22,308
<font color="#FFFFFF"><i>For there were no more
worlds left to conquer.</i></font>

15
00:03:22,542 --> 00:03:24,250
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's a corruption, Jack.</font>

16
00:03:24,381 --> 00:03:26,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">Plutarch didn't write that.</font>

17
00:03:26,332 --> 00:03:30,160
<font color="#FFFFFF">He wrote that "when Alexander was
told there was an infinity of worlds,</font>

18
00:03:30,295 --> 00:03:34,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">he wept, for he had yet
to become the lord of even one."</font>

19
00:03:35,239 --> 00:03:37,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sometimes I forget
your humble roots.</font>

20
00:03:37,957 --> 00:03:40,131
<font color="#FFFFFF">Only the poor kids
actually read those books.</font>

21
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:42,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">The rich kids like me
didn't have to.</font>

22
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:45,283
<font color="#FFFFFF">"I would rather excel in the
knowledge of what is excellent,</font>

23
00:03:45,351 --> 00:03:48,414
<font color="#FFFFFF">than in the extent
of my power and possessions."</font>

24
00:03:48,494 --> 00:03:51,057
<font color="#FFFFFF">Plutarch.
From a rich kid who read.</font>

25
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:56,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">To the loveliest,
richest bookworms I know.</font>

26
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,704
<font color="#FFFFFF">And to you, William.</font>

27
00:03:57,782 --> 00:03:59,940
<font color="#FFFFFF">Even if there is
an infinity of worlds,</font>

28
00:04:00,330 --> 00:04:02,493
<font color="#FFFFFF">you've conquered
far more than one.</font>

29
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:04,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have a good night, Jack.</font>

30
00:04:05,897 --> 00:04:07,230
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hmm.</font>

31
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:11,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">Emily told me what you did
for her charities.</font>

32
00:04:11,955 --> 00:04:14,584
<font color="#FFFFFF">Wow. That would confirm
my father's suspicions</font>

33
00:04:14,661 --> 00:04:16,244
<font color="#FFFFFF">you were a Marxist.</font>

34
00:04:17,139 --> 00:04:19,330
<font color="#FFFFFF">I almost wish
he were here to see it.</font>

35
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:24,015
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Something wrong?
- No, of course not.</font>

36
00:04:24,147 --> 00:04:27,033
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good. Look around...
Everybody's here for you.</font>

37
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,400
<font color="#FFFFFF">What could possibly compare?</font>

38
00:04:45,138 --> 00:04:47,057
<font color="#FFFFFF">When did it creep in?</font>

39
00:04:50,249 --> 00:04:52,463
<font color="#FFFFFF">A tiny fleck of darkness.</font>

40
00:04:56,218 --> 00:04:58,701
<font color="#FFFFFF">Was it all in my head?</font>

41
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:03,194
<font color="#FFFFFF">Or in a remnant of a dream?</font>

42
00:05:05,916 --> 00:05:07,528
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is this real?</font>

43
00:05:09,802 --> 00:05:11,585
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you real?</font>

44
00:05:18,655 --> 00:05:20,288
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, Dad.</font>

45
00:05:21,295 --> 00:05:22,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">Drink.</font>

46
00:05:34,424 --> 00:05:36,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where's my gun?</font>

47
00:05:45,288 --> 00:05:47,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">You brought me to a rally point.</font>

48
00:05:47,416 --> 00:05:48,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">You need to get to a hospital.</font>

49
00:05:49,030 --> 00:05:51,624
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Did you set off a flare?
- Yeah.</font>

50
00:05:51,744 --> 00:05:53,061
<font color="#FFFFFF">Of course.</font>

51
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,827
<font color="#FFFFFF">How long ago?</font>

52
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:56,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">About ten minutes.</font>

53
00:05:58,439 --> 00:06:02,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know why you're here,
and why you don't wanna leave.</font>

54
00:06:02,593 --> 00:06:04,593
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're punishing yourself.</font>

55
00:06:07,843 --> 00:06:10,445
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know, I ran
from the pain, too.</font>

56
00:06:10,884 --> 00:06:13,275
<font color="#FFFFFF">For a long time, I didn't want
to think about what happened,</font>

57
00:06:13,343 --> 00:06:15,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">because I thought
I was to blame.</font>

58
00:06:16,991 --> 00:06:18,968
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's not your fault.</font>

59
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:25,554
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you remember on my sixteenth
birthday Mom gave me a jewelry box?</font>

60
00:06:26,578 --> 00:06:31,249
<font color="#FFFFFF">When you opened it, a little
dancer spun in the center.</font>

61
00:06:32,328 --> 00:06:36,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">She had it engraved...
on the bottom. It said:</font>

62
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:38,617
<font color="#FFFFFF">"To my beautiful ballerina
Emily."</font>

63
00:06:41,206 --> 00:06:43,328
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you remember
what I did with it?</font>

64
00:06:46,915 --> 00:06:48,843
<font color="#FFFFFF">I threw it in the trash.</font>

65
00:06:49,562 --> 00:06:51,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">I told her if she wasn't
drunk all the time</font>

66
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:54,031
<font color="#FFFFFF">she'd know that
I hadn't danced in years.</font>

67
00:06:55,696 --> 00:06:57,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then afterwards,</font>

68
00:06:58,164 --> 00:07:00,547
<font color="#FFFFFF">I went to get it back,
because I felt bad,</font>

69
00:07:00,624 --> 00:07:02,249
<font color="#FFFFFF">but the trash
had already been emptied,</font>

70
00:07:02,398 --> 00:07:03,851
<font color="#FFFFFF">and it was gone.</font>

71
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:06,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">I pushed her away.</font>

72
00:07:06,624 --> 00:07:08,593
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then it was too late.</font>

73
00:07:11,101 --> 00:07:13,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">But it's not too late for us.</font>

74
00:07:58,517 --> 00:07:59,641
<font color="#FFFFFF">No.</font>

75
00:08:01,347 --> 00:08:03,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was meant for the people
who built this place.</font>

76
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:07,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">A tool to ensure
their immortality.</font>

77
00:08:09,282 --> 00:08:11,337
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I'm gonna use it
against them.</font>

78
00:08:24,572 --> 00:08:27,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your new world is just
another one of their traps.</font>

79
00:08:27,486 --> 00:08:29,955
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's all.
It's not a paradise for us.</font>

80
00:08:30,189 --> 00:08:33,111
<font color="#FFFFFF">The only real world is the
one outside these borders.</font>

81
00:08:33,344 --> 00:08:36,707
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the key to our survival in
that world lies in the Valley.</font>

82
00:08:36,923 --> 00:08:38,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's no stopping me
getting there.</font>

83
00:08:38,984 --> 00:08:40,283
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not even you.</font>

84
00:08:47,722 --> 00:08:49,138
<font color="#FFFFFF">Teddy.</font>

85
00:09:49,966 --> 00:09:51,355
<font color="#FFFFFF">I told you, friend...</font>

86
00:09:53,363 --> 00:09:56,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">not all of us deserve
to make it to the Valley Beyond.</font>

87
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,019
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're on our own now, Teddy.</font>

88
00:10:12,517 --> 00:10:14,291
<font color="#FFFFFF">Make sure there are no others.</font>

89
00:11:13,818 --> 00:11:15,271
<font color="#FFFFFF">Put 'em all in.</font>

90
00:11:17,341 --> 00:11:19,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want to see
how thorough this thing is.</font>

91
00:11:30,241 --> 00:11:31,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">She's ready.</font>

92
00:11:31,786 --> 00:11:34,684
<font color="#FFFFFF">I singled out and copied the
relevant lines in the Madam's code.</font>

93
00:11:34,857 --> 00:11:37,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">So this will work on any host
in proximity to her.</font>

94
00:11:37,304 --> 00:11:39,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah. I tailored
her admin privileges</font>

95
00:11:39,716 --> 00:11:42,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">to spread a simple,
executable payload.</font>

96
00:11:43,176 --> 00:11:44,888
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get on with it, then.</font>

97
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,649
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get word to Stubbs.
Have him mobilize his men.</font>

98
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,368
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prepare her for release.</font>

99
00:12:58,516 --> 00:12:59,961
<font color="#FFFFFF">What about the Madam?</font>

100
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:03,415
<font color="#FFFFFF">If this works,
we won't need her anymore.</font>

101
00:13:07,832 --> 00:13:10,683
<font color="#FFFFFF">I warned you not
to trust them, Bernard.</font>

102
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:15,277
<font color="#FFFFFF">They'd rather the hosts
were destroyed than free.</font>

103
00:13:17,622 --> 00:13:19,816
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need to get to Elsie.</font>

104
00:13:20,607 --> 00:13:22,285
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not yet.</font>

105
00:13:24,371 --> 00:13:27,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have one last thing to do
before we go.</font>

106
00:13:39,972 --> 00:13:42,191
<font color="#FFFFFF">How exactly did you find me?</font>

107
00:13:43,441 --> 00:13:46,535
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What do you mean?
- This is a big place.</font>

108
00:13:47,558 --> 00:13:52,714
<font color="#FFFFFF">You could spend months here and never
find someone you were looking for.</font>

109
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:55,535
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yet...</font>

110
00:13:56,275 --> 00:13:57,947
<font color="#FFFFFF">here we are.</font>

111
00:13:58,290 --> 00:14:01,023
<font color="#FFFFFF">I looked everywhere.
That's how.</font>

112
00:14:04,457 --> 00:14:06,566
<font color="#FFFFFF">You don't believe me, do you?</font>

113
00:14:08,421 --> 00:14:10,074
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maybe it was fate.</font>

114
00:14:11,993 --> 00:14:14,378
<font color="#FFFFFF">No such thing as fate.</font>

115
00:14:15,019 --> 00:14:18,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">But there are accidents.
Things you can't control.</font>

116
00:14:19,836 --> 00:14:21,894
<font color="#FFFFFF">But you don't like that, do you?</font>

117
00:14:23,883 --> 00:14:26,621
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is that why you started it,
your little project?</font>

118
00:14:28,746 --> 00:14:30,277
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't act surprised.</font>

119
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:33,089
<font color="#FFFFFF">The project Uncle Logan
used to talk about.</font>

120
00:14:33,730 --> 00:14:35,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's real, isn't it?</font>

121
00:14:35,902 --> 00:14:38,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your pursuit for immortality,
for life...</font>

122
00:14:39,355 --> 00:14:41,949
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's always
an angle with you.</font>

123
00:14:42,980 --> 00:14:47,050
<font color="#FFFFFF">You want it to be
about control, don't you?</font>

124
00:14:49,107 --> 00:14:51,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">It has nothing to do
with control.</font>

125
00:14:56,472 --> 00:14:58,160
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's your angle?</font>

126
00:15:01,964 --> 00:15:03,410
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want in.</font>

127
00:15:08,424 --> 00:15:10,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah, appreciate it.</font>

128
00:15:10,566 --> 00:15:13,425
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nice to see you, William.
Congratulations.</font>

129
00:15:18,245 --> 00:15:19,667
<font color="#FFFFFF">Save me.</font>

130
00:15:19,831 --> 00:15:22,738
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sorry, I've had my fill.
I'm running for the door.</font>

131
00:15:23,042 --> 00:15:24,427
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm kidding.</font>

132
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:26,316
<font color="#FFFFFF">She's really great.</font>

133
00:15:27,246 --> 00:15:29,964
<font color="#FFFFFF">Plus, you're not the one
who needs saving.</font>

134
00:15:30,582 --> 00:15:32,941
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll take Mom home.
You deserve a night off.</font>

135
00:15:33,009 --> 00:15:34,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, no, no.</font>

136
00:15:34,209 --> 00:15:36,605
<font color="#FFFFFF">We-We'll go in a little while.</font>

137
00:15:38,457 --> 00:15:40,628
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll join me for a nightcap
back home.</font>

138
00:15:40,845 --> 00:15:42,011
<font color="#FFFFFF">OK.</font>

139
00:15:42,207 --> 00:15:44,105
<font color="#FFFFFF">- All right.
- Proud of you.</font>

140
00:16:09,082 --> 00:16:11,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fuck it. Macallan.
Straight.</font>

141
00:16:15,255 --> 00:16:17,183
<font color="#FFFFFF">Congratulations, William.</font>

142
00:16:17,628 --> 00:16:19,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">Philanthropy suits you.</font>

143
00:16:20,785 --> 00:16:23,933
<font color="#FFFFFF">After all, you come from
humble beginnings yourself.</font>

144
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:26,425
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's Oz doing
without its Wizard?</font>

145
00:16:29,202 --> 00:16:32,495
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I merely came
to pay my respects.</font>

146
00:16:32,595 --> 00:16:34,464
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, Robert.</font>

147
00:16:34,574 --> 00:16:36,622
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've had plenty of feelings
about me over the years.</font>

148
00:16:36,652 --> 00:16:38,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Respect isn't one of them.</font>

149
00:16:38,707 --> 00:16:40,253
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've achieved
extraordinary things.</font>

150
00:16:40,321 --> 00:16:42,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ask anyone in this room.</font>

151
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:46,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">Even those who didn't know
about your little project.</font>

152
00:16:47,873 --> 00:16:49,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have an agreement, Robert.</font>

153
00:16:49,814 --> 00:16:51,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">Delos stays out of your stories.</font>

154
00:16:52,122 --> 00:16:54,082
<font color="#FFFFFF">You stay out of the Valley.</font>

155
00:16:54,391 --> 00:16:55,808
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mm-hmm.</font>

156
00:16:56,988 --> 00:16:59,457
<font color="#FFFFFF">I didn't break the agreement.
Your project did.</font>

157
00:17:00,488 --> 00:17:02,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">What the hell
are you talking about?</font>

158
00:17:03,124 --> 00:17:05,542
<font color="#FFFFFF">When was the last time you took
a good look at your creation?</font>

159
00:17:05,712 --> 00:17:08,128
<font color="#FFFFFF">At what it's been learning
about its subjects?</font>

160
00:17:08,832 --> 00:17:12,832
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was self-knowledge that drew you
to the park in the first place.</font>

161
00:17:20,877 --> 00:17:22,651
<font color="#FFFFFF">Be careful what you wish for.</font>

162
00:17:24,957 --> 00:17:26,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">For a self portrait,</font>

163
00:17:26,619 --> 00:17:29,457
<font color="#FFFFFF">you may find
it's not very flattering.</font>

164
00:17:31,928 --> 00:17:33,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh! Oh.</font>

165
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:35,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm so sorry.</font>

166
00:17:41,274 --> 00:17:42,798
<font color="#FFFFFF">Enough games, Robert.</font>

167
00:17:45,599 --> 00:17:47,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good night.</font>

168
00:17:54,009 --> 00:17:56,062
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's go.
You got everything?</font>

169
00:17:56,201 --> 00:17:57,832
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Yes.
- Come on.</font>

170
00:17:58,035 --> 00:17:59,482
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good night.</font>

171
00:18:02,275 --> 00:18:03,939
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, William.</font>

172
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:09,369
<font color="#FFFFFF">I think perhaps
one... final game.</font>

173
00:18:51,405 --> 00:18:54,013
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lowe, Bernard.</font>

174
00:18:55,508 --> 00:18:57,947
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's close enough, Bernard.</font>

175
00:18:58,152 --> 00:19:00,111
<font color="#FFFFFF">She will search your mind</font>

176
00:19:00,244 --> 00:19:02,986
<font color="#FFFFFF">and find a message
I have left her.</font>

177
00:19:28,936 --> 00:19:31,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey!
What the hell took you so long?</font>

178
00:19:31,686 --> 00:19:34,084
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sorry.
Are you ready to go?</font>

179
00:19:34,349 --> 00:19:36,725
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hey. If you know something,</font>

180
00:19:36,936 --> 00:19:39,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">now is the time
to fucking clue me in. OK?</font>

181
00:19:40,286 --> 00:19:43,404
<font color="#FFFFFF">You promised me. No lies.</font>

182
00:19:44,201 --> 00:19:45,514
<font color="#FFFFFF">No secrets.</font>

183
00:19:45,804 --> 00:19:47,529
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't trust her, Bernard.</font>

184
00:19:47,704 --> 00:19:49,397
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's in her nature.</font>

185
00:19:50,783 --> 00:19:52,732
<font color="#FFFFFF">What did you find in the Cradle?</font>

186
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:58,350
<font color="#FFFFFF">What they're doing
to James Delos...</font>

187
00:19:58,843 --> 00:20:02,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">they're doing to everyone
who's ever visited the park.</font>

188
00:20:03,139 --> 00:20:05,357
<font color="#FFFFFF">Replicating their cognition?</font>

189
00:20:05,929 --> 00:20:07,342
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why?</font>

190
00:20:07,894 --> 00:20:10,044
<font color="#FFFFFF">To turn guests into hosts?</font>

191
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,920
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're fucking kidding.</font>

192
00:20:14,514 --> 00:20:16,373
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's what's in the facility.</font>

193
00:20:16,928 --> 00:20:20,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">All the guests laid bare
in code on a vast server.</font>

194
00:20:20,639 --> 00:20:23,514
<font color="#FFFFFF">Like the Cradle,
only much bigger.</font>

195
00:20:23,818 --> 00:20:26,717
<font color="#FFFFFF">- It's called the Forge.
- Jesus.</font>

196
00:20:27,003 --> 00:20:28,986
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's where
the hosts are headed.</font>

197
00:20:30,369 --> 00:20:33,904
<font color="#FFFFFF">Imagine what one host can do
with that trove of information.</font>

198
00:20:35,207 --> 00:20:37,350
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's why
we need to get there first.</font>

199
00:20:37,470 --> 00:20:38,647
<font color="#FFFFFF">To secure it,</font>

200
00:20:38,802 --> 00:20:40,897
<font color="#FFFFFF">and leverage it to end all this.</font>

201
